st_car\"><\/span>What adds up to the qualities of the fastest car?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\r\n<p>Approximately 360 km is the top speed of certain cars, whereas just 150 km is the top speed of others. Have you ever considered the variables that affect a car&#8217;s top speed? A car&#8217;s speed depends on a number of variables.<br \/>However, the top six influencing elements are here. It is they<\/p>\r\n<h4><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"1_Engine_Performance\"><\/span>1. Engine Performance<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h4>\r\n<p>Yes, the power of your engine is the most crucial component. More potential for speed conversion exists when the engine is more powerful. But how do you translate engine power into speed? For the solution, read the next factor.<\/p>\r\n<h4><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"2_Geared_ratio\"><\/span>2. Geared ratio<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h4>\r\n<p>The tools that manipulate speed and torque are known as gears (since the product of speed and torque is the power). They are in charge of turning torque into speed (however the power remains the same). Less torque is available to the tyres at higher speeds for a given vehicle.<\/p>\r\n<p>It comes as no surprise that when driving up mountains, we shift into first or second gear to receive less speed but more power. Therefore, the speed of our car will increase as the gear ratio does.<\/p>\r\n<h4><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"3_The_car%E2%80%99s_weight\"><\/span>3. The car&#8217;s weight<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h4>\r\n<p>Without a doubt, a vehicle&#8217;s payload determines its top speed. Automobiles with higher payloads will travel at slower speeds than cars with lower payloads.<\/p>\r\n<h4><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"4_Vehicle_aerodynamics\"><\/span>4. Vehicle aerodynamics<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h4>\r\n<p>When determining the top speed of the car, aerodynamics is crucial. When air strikes an aerodynamic structure, there is less resistance. There is no doubt as to why racing automobiles are always made streamlined.<\/p>\r\n<h4><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"5_Tire_grip_on_the_surface_of_the_road\"><\/span>5. Tire grip on the surface of the road<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h4>\r\n<p>While an automobile is accelerating to its top speed, the tyres should have enough traction on the pavement.<br \/>Slipping will occur if the tyres lose traction, which will lower speed and shorten tyre life<\/p>\r\n<h4><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"6_The_fuel%E2%80%99s_calorie_content\"><\/span>6. The fuel&#8217;s calorie content<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h4>\r\n<p>The engine always receives greater power from gasoline with a high energy density, which is directly proportional to the car&#8217;s top speed. So never disregard the fuel.<\/p>\r\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Top_10_Fastest_Cars_in_India\"><\/span>Top 10 Fastest Cars in India<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\r\n<p>Manufacturers all around the country are now selling attractive, functioning, fast, and, most importantly, fast automobiles. In India in 2020, here are the top ten fastest automobiles you can buy.<\/p>\r\n<h4><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"1_Porsche_911\"><\/span>1. Porsche 911<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h4>\r\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone  wp-image-2835\" src=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/porchase-1-1-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"703\" height=\"396\" srcset=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/porchase-1-1-300x169.jpg 300w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/porchase-1-1-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/porchase-1-1-768x432.jpg 768w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/porchase-1-1.jpg 12